            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion and carrot have softened, increase the heat to high and add your <strong>lamb mince</strong> to the pan with your <strong>ground cumin </strong>and<strong> chopped garlic</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until browned, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Add the<strong> spicy stock</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min further or until thickened to a bolognese-like consistency – this is your <strong>spicy lamb mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
